Modules The company offers several modules as part of their InsurTech stack for commercial lines of business:

Claim Management

The Claim Management module aims to eliminate manual interventions in the claim process. It features role management, policy master management, dynamic claim form creation, status management, reports, notification, and alerts.

Portfolio Module

The Portfolio Module manages the insurance portfolio of partners, including project or non-project policies, re-insurance patterns, etc.

Certificate Module

The Certificate Module eases the process of certificate requests against policies, auto-reads emails from insurers, and manages the certificate repository for future reference.

Supplier Module

The Supplier Module continuously monitors the supplier ecosystem and risk parameters associated with suppliers, mitigating risk with adequate policies and compliance support.

Asset Module

The Asset Module measures an asset's default potential or market value fluctuation and provides the needed coverage to protect the asset value from unforeseen events.

Segments

GoSure.AI provides a unified, integrated 360° platform for various stakeholders in the insurance industry. The following segments are catered to by GoSure.AI:

Brokers/MGAs and Agents

GoSure.AI provides a unified, integrated 360° platform for brokers and agents to manage their operations and customer engagement. The platform facilitates capturing every single data point and generating invaluable insights into the business and customer behavior.

Adjusters

GoSure.AI provides a unified, integrated 360° platform for adjusters to manage both their back office and field operations seamlessly by connecting with the insured as well as the requestors.

Carriers and Reinsurers

GoSure.AI provides a unified, integrated 360° platform for carriers to empower their last mile distribution partners, such as brokers and agents, with adequate technology. The platform also provides embedded insurance capabilities and portals for all stakeholders.

Enterprises

GoSure.AI provides a unified, integrated 360° platform for enterprises to track all insurable assets, assess the risk, know the risk score, plan for mitigating the risks, and then manage.

GoSure's 360° digital insurance platform

The platform is a comprehensive, end-to-end solution for commercial insurance.

It offers a range of features and benefits that transform the insurance process, from new business acquisition to policy servicing.

Key benefits and features:

1\. Enhanced Customer Experience with Cognitive Data Ingestion

The platform uses cognitive data ingestion to provide a personalized and intuitive experience for customers.

This enables customers to easily access and manage their policies, claims, and other insurance-related information.

2\. Growth opportunities with new embedded or industry-specific programs

The platform offers opportunities for insurers to create new, industry-specific programs or embedded insurance products.

This enables insurers to expand their offerings, increase revenue, and stay competitive in the market.

3\. Accelerated time-to-market with built-in insurance modules

The platform comes with pre-built insurance modules that can be easily configured and deployed.

This accelerates the time-to-market for new insurance products, enabling insurers to quickly respond to changing market conditions.

4\. Improved quality and productivity by streamlined communication

The platform streamlines communication between insurers, brokers, and customers, reducing errors and increasing efficiency.

This leads to improved quality and productivity, as well as faster resolution of claims and other insurance-related issues.

5\. Delivery of more value to customers with needed visibility on their data

The platform provides customers with transparency and visibility into their insurance data, enabling them to make informed decisions.

This leads to increased customer satisfaction and loyalty, as customers feel more in control of their insurance experience.

6\. Reduced total cost of ownership with a SAAS model

The platform is offered as a Software-as-a-Service (SAAS) model, which reduces the total cost of ownership for insurers.

This means that insurers can access the platform without having to invest in expensive hardware, software, or infrastructure.

Overall, GoSure's 360° digital insurance platform is designed to transform the commercial insurance industry by providing a seamless, efficient, and customer-centric experience. By leveraging cognitive data ingestion, built-in insurance modules, and streamlined communication, the platform enables insurers to drive growth, improve productivity, and deliver more value to customers.
